  "Lead levels in children's blood dropped by 75% after lead was removed from gasoline. Which environmental law and what policy approach made this possible?": "",
  "The Clean Air Act through command-and-control regulation phasing out leaded gasoline": "",
  "The Safe Drinking Water Act through voluntary compliance": "",
  "CERCLA through Superfund site cleanups": "",
  "TSCA through voluntary industry agreements": "",
  "The Clean Air Act's regulatory phase-out of leaded gasoline is one of the greatest public health achievements of environmental regulation, demonstrating how command-and-control standards can produce dramatic health benefits that far exceed compliance costs.": "",
  "An industry group argues that a new EPA regulation will cost $1 billion per year. An environmental group counters that it will prevent $30 billion in health and environmental damages. What analytical framework is being applied?": "",
  "Cost-benefit analysis comparing compliance costs against health and environmental benefits": "",
  "Stakeholder analysis, particularly regarding ratio in most standard conditions": "",
